

=Bio=

Robert co-founded Ethos in 2010 after more than 20 years in senior corporate positions with organisations including IBM, Ernst & Young and Thales where he managed several divisional level businesses as well as technology startups. Having held key roles in strategy, business development and delivery Robert’s experience covers a very broad spectrum of business issues including effective go-to-market strategies, change management, knowledge management, effective collaboration and team building, all of which experience he continues to employ with Ethos clients today.

For over a decade now Robert has been exploring and implementing new and innovative problem solving approaches enabled by the hyper-connectivity of the Internet. His enthusiasm for improvement through innovation is infectious and he thrives when taking on the challenge of a complex, multi-sided problem.

Robert has a degree in Computer Science and technology remains a passion in all aspects of his life. When not working he enjoys running, gardening and DIY. He is not often found without at least one book on the go and loves to spend time with his wife and three young boys.

